    <h4>23 April 2014</h4>
    <h2><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/sell-on-etsy/id860815329?mt=8">Sell on Etsy</a> launched in six languages</h2>
    
    <div class="columns">

      <p>A critical part of the work at <a href="http://www.etsy.com">Etsy</a> is building tools to help sellers grow their Etsy shops. Our sellers spend a lot of time in workshops, studios, or at in-person marketplaces, and running an Etsy business should fit seamlessly into their lives. With <em>Sell on Etsy</em> we were able to do just that.</p>

      <p>We packed in a tremendous amount of functionality in the first version of the app. Sellers recieve push notifications, a shop activity feed and shop stats. They&apos;re able to fill orders, respond to Etsy conversations, create new items or renew older ones.</p>

      <p>We tried to make the app feel light and airy &ndash; highlighting only the seller&apos;s items and the buyer activity around those items. Working with <a href="https://dribbble.com/mdeckert">Melissa Deckert</a> and <a href="http://samuelsherman.tumblr.com/">Samuel Sherman</a> of Etsy&apos;s Global Design Studio we were able to create impressive visual flourishes that were unmistakably Etsy without visually weighing down the user interface. We worked with Oak who provided <a href="http://blog.symbolset.com/sell-on-etsy">a set of icons</a>.</p>

      <p><em>Sell on Etsy</em> is a version 1.0 app that supports both iOS 6 and 7. We even launched internationally translating the app into six languages. We look forward to adding features and perfecting the ones that are already there.</p>

      <p>Thanks to the team including <a href="https://twitter.com/jeyb">Jey Biddulph</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/amyinspace">Amy Dyer</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/lacyrhoades">Lacy Rhodes</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/thescottostler">Scott Ostler</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/podduturi">Arpan Podduturi</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/BritWills">Brittany Williams</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/jennylow">Jen Macchiarelli</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/pchensoftware">Peter Chen</a> and many more at Etsy.</p>
    </div>
